txt.en: Rumours have reached the ears of the Rangers at Esteldín that a chieftain has arisen within the ranks of the Wargs at Dol Dínen, uniting the packs.
You have defeated Raugzok, chief among the Wargs of Dol Dínen

You become aware of a presence; a chieftain has risen up among the Wargs of Dol Dínen, uniting the packs that run with the Orcs gathered there. Even a tenuous unity among such foul beasts is a danger to all.\n\nYou should slay the chieftain of the Wargs and shatter the courage of these beasts. The vile creatures linger near the Orcs, protecting their masters, and as such you will need the strength of allies to fight along with you.
Raugzok, chief of the Wargs, can be found at Dol Dínen in the south-eastern North Downs.\n\nYou should defeat Raugzok.
You have defeated Raugzok, chief among the Wargs of Dol Dínen. Your efforts have done much to preserve the North Downs from the ravages of war.

'Do not venture too deeply into Dol Dínen. The danger would be too great, even for your fellowship.'
'One less leader walks amongst the Wargs, thanks to you.'
'You have slain the chieftain of the Wargs of Dol Dínen, and within his own den. Your courage is great, [placeholder].'
